  "prompt": "What is the best time of day to drink a single coffee to keep you going for the longest duration?",
  "response": "The best time of day to drink coffee for sustained energy typically falls between 9:30 AM and 11:30 AM. This timing aligns with the body's natural circadian rhythm, where cortisol levels\u2014responsible for alertness\u2014are on the decline after peaking in the early morning. Drinking coffee during this window can help to enhance alertness and focus without interfering too much with your body's natural processes.\n\nMoreover, drinking coffee too late in the day may disrupt sleep, which can lead to fatigue the following day. To maximize the benefits, consider moderation and timing based on your individual routine and sensitivity to caffeine. Each person's reaction to caffeine can vary, so it's important to pay attention to how your body responds to find the optimal time for you.",
